<title>BRAZIL: Brazil Furnas sale set to go ahead in 1997.</title>
<headline>Brazil Furnas sale set to go ahead in 1997.</headline>
<dateline>BRASILIA 1996-11-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The sell-off of Brazilian power generator  Furnas is set to go ahead after the Senate allowed the firm to hive off its nuclear unit, said Jose Pio Borges, privatization chief of the National Development Bank (BNDES).</p>
<p>Pio Borges told reporters after a meeting of the National Privatization Council (CND) that Furnas's nuclear power interests would be transferred to the government's nuclear power agency Nuclen on January 1.</p>
<p>Furnas and Eletrosul will be the first of Brazil's four power generators to be sold off, possibly by late 1997.</p>
<p>-- Michael Christie, Brasilia Newsroom 55-61-2230358</p>
